[Verse 3: L.I.F.E. Long]
New York, New York notorious for dreams seen
Camouflage regime on the paper chase (Money) for the money (Money)
(Green) Sever your thoughts, get caught with the infrared
Beams—bloodspots on foreheads from the red dots
Aiming, marking my position from the Rotten Apple’s
Heart: Jamaica, Queens.  Rock out my socks, feel
The vibe transmitted from speakers out parks, or hear the
BX (The BX.  Kool Herc first sparked)
The flame spread, burning up the Five Boroughs
Q-U, Brooknam, Shaolin, L.I., L.E.-
-S. to Y-O.  The streets of New York scored by Kool G
Rap & DJ Polo.  Watch your back from sheisty po-po
Stop-and-frisking pigs in blue wearing badges
Quick to cap a couple of cabbages.  Murals cover
Walls of those slain by savages.  Graffiti, wild starving
Artists using trains as canvas from [?] to Barclay

